+// Apple's storage stack treats F_FULLFSYNC as a global drive barrier
+// (whichever fd it's issued on). Phase 1's probe on this host
+// measured F_FULLFSYNC p50 = 4.0 ms (vs. fsync() p50 = 17 us); the
+// sync-write numbers measured here will track the F_FULLFSYNC class,
+// which is the apples-to-apples comparison vs. Linux ext4 fsync
+// (3.6 ms p50 on the project's reference Linux VM).
